How to export the WebSite developed on Google Site?

Userful Link: https://www.steegle.com/google-sites/how-to/export-with-takeout

The key word is：Google Takeout

Google Takeout is a project by the Google Data Liberation Front that allows users of Google products, such as YouTube and Gmail, to export their data to a downloadable archive file.

The simplified steps are:

  1. Duplicate the Google site on Google Drive

  2. Create a new folder named ABC on Google Drive

  3. Move duplicated google site to the folder ABC

  4. Use google takeout to archive the folder ABC (Note you need to deselect all the item and only select the ABC folder in Google Drive)

  5. For the archive option, I usually use the link to download. Actually you can directly download the files at the end of process

After the above steps, you will get all the files for the website you want to export. Then you can deploy them onto any Host server and DNS server. For my case, I am using AWS S3 and ASW Router53.
